1
00:01:29,460 --> 00:01:34,910
[Our Dazzling Days]

2
00:01:35,320 --> 00:01:37,740
[Episode 14]

3
00:01:41,680 --> 00:01:42,680
Sit down, please.

4
00:01:50,000 --> 00:01:50,640
So...

5
00:01:51,680 --> 00:01:53,210
What should we do, Xiaoman?

6
00:02:43,870 --> 00:02:45,520
No need to give this much compensation.

7
00:02:45,520 --> 00:02:46,360
Seriously?

8
00:02:46,360 --> 00:02:48,490
I'm even worried this won't be enough.

9
00:02:49,960 --> 00:02:51,450
You can't pay it yourself.

10
00:02:56,500 --> 00:02:58,030
Take this.

11
00:02:58,800 --> 00:02:59,730
Just put it away.

12
00:03:00,310 --> 00:03:00,840
Take it.

13
00:03:00,860 --> 00:03:01,400
No need.

14
00:03:01,710 --> 00:03:03,910
No, I can't let you pay this by yourself.

15
00:03:04,800 --> 00:03:05,260
Take it.

16
00:03:05,680 --> 00:03:06,520
You keep it.

17
00:03:06,520 --> 00:03:07,360
I have enough.

18
00:03:07,360 --> 00:03:08,310
I have enough.

19
00:03:08,590 --> 00:03:10,520
It's okay. Don't worry about this.

20
00:03:13,360 --> 00:03:15,150
When we get there, be polite.

21
00:03:15,360 --> 00:03:16,310
Don't just go there

22
00:03:16,310 --> 00:03:17,710
and act like a fool.

23
00:03:18,470 --> 00:03:20,770
C-Call them bro
or whatever is appropriate.

24
00:03:20,770 --> 00:03:22,910
Apologize properly and be respectful.

25
00:03:22,910 --> 00:03:23,960
I didn't expect it

26
00:03:25,310 --> 00:03:26,510
to turn out like this.

27
00:03:29,710 --> 00:03:31,490
"Summer Vacation Plan for Shanghai"?

28
00:03:31,490 --> 00:03:32,329
What's this?

29
00:03:33,590 --> 00:03:34,990
Forget about that thing.

30
00:03:35,280 --> 00:03:37,700
After you pay this,
how are you supposed to go to Shanghai?

31
00:03:37,700 --> 00:03:38,550
I'm not going to Shanghai.

32
00:03:38,550 --> 00:03:40,240
Let's settle the problem
in front of us first.

33
00:03:40,240 --> 00:03:42,040
Forget about going to Shanghai.

34
00:03:44,120 --> 00:03:44,870
Eight.

35
00:03:46,079 --> 00:03:46,870
Nine.

36
00:03:47,750 --> 00:03:48,750
Ten.

37
00:03:50,250 --> 00:03:51,690
This is 200.

38
00:03:57,150 --> 00:03:58,000
Thirty-six.

39
00:03:58,540 --> 00:03:59,400
Thirty-seven.

40
00:04:10,430 --> 00:04:11,400
I'd like to make a call.

41
00:04:11,400 --> 00:04:12,360
Okay, go ahead.

42
00:04:33,360 --> 00:04:35,070
Hello, um...

43
00:04:35,070 --> 00:04:37,720
I'm looking for Yan Xiaodan in Room 303.

44
00:04:39,270 --> 00:04:40,270
Great, thank you.

45
00:04:44,190 --> 00:04:45,680
Hello, Xiaodan.

46
00:04:46,070 --> 00:04:47,720
It's me. What are you doing?

47
00:04:48,480 --> 00:04:50,020
Waiting for my roommates
to go out together.

48
00:04:50,020 --> 00:04:50,880
Have you eaten?

49
00:04:52,310 --> 00:04:53,920
Just finished my meal.
You haven't eaten again?

50
00:04:53,920 --> 00:04:54,630
I've eaten.

51
00:04:56,040 --> 00:04:57,570
I ate at Uncle Ding's place.

52
00:04:58,070 --> 00:04:59,270
That was really good.

53
00:05:01,760 --> 00:05:03,620
What's wrong? You sound a bit off.

54
00:05:04,440 --> 00:05:05,150
Nothing.

55
00:05:05,240 --> 00:05:08,000
Just hanging around after dinner.

56
00:05:08,030 --> 00:05:09,090
So I'm calling you.

57
00:05:13,870 --> 00:05:16,800
Well, there's something.

58
00:05:18,040 --> 00:05:20,360
We... We...

59
00:05:21,720 --> 00:05:25,480
We might have
a training session this summer.

60
00:05:26,740 --> 00:05:28,140
No, it's a training camp.

61
00:05:29,070 --> 00:05:31,000
Yeah, everyone's going.

62
00:05:31,750 --> 00:05:36,350
So I was thinking I should also go

63
00:05:36,700 --> 00:05:37,480
to learn more

64
00:05:37,480 --> 00:05:39,270
and hone my skills.

65
00:05:40,040 --> 00:05:41,159
If I join them,

66
00:05:41,870 --> 00:05:43,040
I probably won't be able

67
00:05:43,040 --> 00:05:45,920
to visit you in Shanghai
during the summer vacation.

68
00:05:45,920 --> 00:05:47,830
Are you hiding something from me?

69
00:05:48,409 --> 00:05:51,210
Nothing.
It's just this summer training session.

70
00:05:52,220 --> 00:05:54,510
Then I'm coming back this summer vacation.

71
00:05:54,510 --> 00:05:55,640
You're coming back?

72
00:05:56,130 --> 00:05:56,810
Why?

73
00:05:57,560 --> 00:05:58,590
I miss you.

74
00:05:58,950 --> 00:06:00,630
I want to see you.

75
00:06:01,380 --> 00:06:02,380
That's great!

76
00:06:02,800 --> 00:06:04,700
That's right. You should come back.

77
00:06:04,700 --> 00:06:06,250
Nowhere is better than home, right?

78
00:06:06,250 --> 00:06:07,850
It'll be so nice to come home.

79
00:06:07,950 --> 00:06:08,630
So when?

80
00:06:10,870 --> 00:06:11,870
I'll go pick you up then.

81
00:06:11,870 --> 00:06:12,390
Hmm.

82
00:06:12,870 --> 00:06:13,600
I've got to hang up.

83
00:06:13,600 --> 00:06:14,800
They're calling me out.

84
00:06:14,800 --> 00:06:15,800
Okay, go have fun.

85
00:06:16,480 --> 00:06:18,740
No problem. Call me if you need anything.

86
00:06:18,870 --> 00:06:19,510
Yeah.

87
00:06:37,310 --> 00:06:38,040
Take it slow.

88
00:06:46,040 --> 00:06:47,500
Over there. Here he comes.

89
00:06:48,230 --> 00:06:49,960
He's coming!

90
00:06:50,390 --> 00:06:51,390
Here, we're here.

91
00:06:52,190 --> 00:06:53,680
Xiaodan! Xia Lei!

92
00:06:55,800 --> 00:06:56,510
Here, here.

93
00:06:57,190 --> 00:06:58,159
Look over here. Here!

94
00:06:58,159 --> 00:06:59,130
We're here!

95
00:07:03,750 --> 00:07:04,390
Come on.

96
00:07:04,390 --> 00:07:05,000
Xiaoman.

97
00:07:05,190 --> 00:07:06,000
-Come on.
-Xiaoman, Xiaoman.

98
00:07:06,000 --> 00:07:07,260
Help me. Give me a hand.

99
00:07:07,430 --> 00:07:08,760
-Give it to me.
-Come on.

100
00:07:09,160 --> 00:07:10,060
Give it to me. Let go.

101
00:07:10,060 --> 00:07:11,260
Let go. You can let go.

102
00:07:11,800 --> 00:07:13,160
Come on, be careful.

103
00:07:13,390 --> 00:07:13,950
Dad.

104
00:07:14,040 --> 00:07:14,950
Come on.

105
00:07:15,720 --> 00:07:16,230
Here.

106
00:07:16,600 --> 00:07:17,330
I missed you.

107
00:07:18,630 --> 00:07:19,720
I missed you, too.

108
00:07:20,390 --> 00:07:21,920
You've grown taller again.

109
00:07:22,580 --> 00:07:23,730
No, I haven't.

110
00:07:25,510 --> 00:07:27,800
Alright, you two.
Get in the car and chat there.

111
00:07:27,800 --> 00:07:29,660
Come on, we're in broad daylight.

112
00:07:29,750 --> 00:07:30,390
Let's go.

113
00:07:33,100 --> 00:07:35,100
Xiaodan, you've grown taller, too!

114
00:07:42,600 --> 00:07:44,120
Mom, Dad, I'm home.

115
00:07:44,750 --> 00:07:45,800
I'm also back, Mrs. Tong.

116
00:07:45,800 --> 00:07:46,720
Welcome back.

117
00:07:47,909 --> 00:07:48,640
Where is she?

118
00:07:48,720 --> 00:07:49,159
Over there.

119
00:07:49,159 --> 00:07:49,750
Come on.

120
00:07:50,390 --> 00:07:51,650
It's so clean and neat.

121
00:07:51,940 --> 00:07:52,800
Come on, Xiaodan.

122
00:07:52,800 --> 00:07:54,800
I've changed the bedsheet, duvet cover,

123
00:07:54,800 --> 00:07:56,600
and pillowcase. Everything's new.

124
00:07:56,600 --> 00:07:57,530
I've also got you

125
00:07:57,780 --> 00:07:58,690
the towel and toothbrush.

126
00:07:58,690 --> 00:08:00,890
If you need anything else, just tell me.

127
00:08:02,430 --> 00:08:03,000
No need, Mrs. Tong.

128
00:08:03,000 --> 00:08:04,070
I can just stay at my own house.

129
00:08:04,070 --> 00:08:04,630
That won't do.

130
00:08:04,630 --> 00:08:05,920
Your parents called me

131
00:08:06,000 --> 00:08:08,460
and said they wanted you
to lodge in my place.

132
00:08:09,160 --> 00:08:10,630
That'll cause you so much trouble.

133
00:08:10,630 --> 00:08:11,190
I-I really

134
00:08:11,190 --> 00:08:12,830
can stay at home by myself.

135
00:08:12,830 --> 00:08:13,390
What trouble?

136
00:08:13,390 --> 00:08:14,590
Everything's ready.

137
00:08:14,750 --> 00:08:16,160
Your parents entrusted you to me.

138
00:08:16,160 --> 00:08:17,920
Don't make them worry.

139
00:08:18,390 --> 00:08:19,240
Just stay.

140
00:08:19,340 --> 00:08:21,160
Making your parents feel assured is
what matters most, right?

141
00:08:21,160 --> 00:08:22,070
Then w-where

142
00:08:22,070 --> 00:08:22,920
do I sleep?

143
00:08:23,090 --> 00:08:24,430
On the sofa.

144
00:08:25,010 --> 00:08:26,600
I sleep on the sofa?
That's so uncomfortable. I...

145
00:08:26,600 --> 00:08:28,190
Y-You can g-go
sleep on the kang at my place.

146
00:08:28,190 --> 00:08:28,790
It's okay.

147
00:08:29,800 --> 00:08:32,000
Mrs. Tong, the two of us are heading out.

148
00:08:32,080 --> 00:08:32,750
Let's go.

149
00:08:35,110 --> 00:08:36,080
Where are we going?

150
00:08:36,080 --> 00:08:37,210
Going to your place!

151
00:08:37,240 --> 00:08:38,240
I got it looking so tidy.

152
00:08:38,240 --> 00:08:39,120
Let's go check it out.

153
00:08:39,120 --> 00:08:40,000
There's a surprise, huh?

154
00:08:40,000 --> 00:08:42,200
No surprise. What surprise would there be?

155
00:08:42,200 --> 00:08:42,740
You're lying.

156
00:08:42,740 --> 00:08:44,140
I just cleaned it up a bit.

157
00:08:47,040 --> 00:08:47,640
Come on in.

158
00:08:50,460 --> 00:08:51,690
It's so clean now!

159
00:08:51,720 --> 00:08:52,790
Of course it is.

160
00:08:53,630 --> 00:08:55,360
I came to do cleaning every day.

161
00:08:56,030 --> 00:08:57,960
Good job, clean-up MVP. Let me see.

162
00:09:07,150 --> 00:09:07,790
This...

163
00:09:09,310 --> 00:09:10,500
Is this for me?

164
00:09:13,390 --> 00:09:14,750
I love it so much!

165
00:09:18,100 --> 00:09:19,460
It's amazing.

166
00:09:21,960 --> 00:09:23,030
This is

167
00:09:23,860 --> 00:09:26,720
the platform
where we watched the fireworks, isn't it?

168
00:09:26,720 --> 00:09:27,850
We stood right here,

169
00:09:28,080 --> 00:09:29,100
and the fireworks were here.

170
00:09:29,100 --> 00:09:31,840
Right! And then... Let me see.

171
00:09:33,080 --> 00:09:34,320
And over here.

172
00:09:35,150 --> 00:09:37,790
Right. When we were kids,
we had that fireworks battle

173
00:09:37,790 --> 00:09:39,150
in this corridor.

174
00:09:39,790 --> 00:09:40,870
This...

175
00:09:40,990 --> 00:09:42,630
This is perfectly scaled.

176
00:09:42,650 --> 00:09:44,270
It's even better than what the seniors

177
00:09:44,270 --> 00:09:45,060
at our school can make.

178
00:09:45,060 --> 00:09:45,580
Really?

179
00:09:49,560 --> 00:09:51,960
We've been playing here
since we were kids.

180
00:09:52,080 --> 00:09:53,480
I know what it looks like,

181
00:09:53,630 --> 00:09:54,600
where every pipe is,

182
00:09:54,600 --> 00:09:56,400
and what's missing accurately.

183
00:09:56,790 --> 00:09:57,960
It's so well done.

184
00:09:59,150 --> 00:09:59,910
What's this?

185
00:10:03,790 --> 00:10:04,850
What's happening?

186
00:10:05,750 --> 00:10:06,810
It's working time.

187
00:10:10,340 --> 00:10:10,950
This...

188
00:10:13,390 --> 00:10:14,600
This can even smoke?

189
00:10:14,670 --> 00:10:16,000
Yeah, it has got to work.

190
00:10:16,150 --> 00:10:16,600
Otherwise,

191
00:10:16,600 --> 00:10:18,390
it'd just be a pile of cold metal.

192
00:10:18,390 --> 00:10:19,450
How did you do this?

193
00:10:22,000 --> 00:10:22,800
Do you like it?

194
00:10:23,200 --> 00:10:23,960
I do.

195
00:10:27,790 --> 00:10:28,590
You like this?

196
00:10:32,550 --> 00:10:34,950
This must have taken you
a long time to make.

197
00:10:36,790 --> 00:10:37,520
A few months.

198
00:10:39,940 --> 00:10:40,730
Thank you.

199
00:10:41,900 --> 00:10:42,730
For what?

200
00:10:49,600 --> 00:10:50,730
I'm glad you like it.

201
00:10:54,820 --> 00:10:56,840
[Xiaodan]

202
00:11:05,630 --> 00:11:07,630
Come on. Come inside. Welcome back.

203
00:11:08,360 --> 00:11:09,360
We're back.

204
00:11:09,790 --> 00:11:11,580
It's been a while since I was here.

205
00:11:11,580 --> 00:11:12,670
It's so good to be back.

206
00:11:12,670 --> 00:11:14,270
It feels cozy to be back here.

207
00:11:15,550 --> 00:11:16,690
I-I'll light some incense.

208
00:11:16,690 --> 00:11:17,600
Haven't seen Mrs. Zhang in a while.

209
00:11:17,600 --> 00:11:18,960
Grandma, Xiaodan is here.

210
00:11:18,960 --> 00:11:20,150
Mrs. Zhang, I'm back.

211
00:11:20,150 --> 00:11:21,750
Why didn't you also tell her
about my return?

212
00:11:21,750 --> 00:11:23,440
You're right in front of her.
What's there for me to say?

213
00:11:23,440 --> 00:11:24,900
Mrs. Zhang, I'm back, too.

214
00:11:24,970 --> 00:11:26,830
Let me light some incense for you.

215
00:11:30,280 --> 00:11:32,400
Why did you put the drawing
I gave you up there?

216
00:11:32,400 --> 00:11:33,910
I put it there,
so every day when I hit the sack,

217
00:11:33,910 --> 00:11:34,790
I can see it.

218
00:11:35,390 --> 00:11:36,600
What about the other drawings?

219
00:11:36,600 --> 00:11:37,750
They're all here.

220
00:11:37,770 --> 00:11:40,200
It's a rotating exhibition.
I don't just display this single one.

221
00:11:40,200 --> 00:11:41,600
I change them on a weekly basis,

222
00:11:41,600 --> 00:11:43,110
sticking a new one every Monday.

223
00:11:43,110 --> 00:11:44,040
Just put it here.

224
00:11:44,220 --> 00:11:46,080
They're all here. Let me show you.

225
00:11:49,670 --> 00:11:52,070
Look, this one is here.

226
00:11:52,290 --> 00:11:53,890
I sealed it with clear tape.

227
00:11:54,090 --> 00:11:55,150
It won't get dirty.

228
00:11:56,160 --> 00:11:57,620
This one is from last week.

229
00:11:58,360 --> 00:12:00,020
I'll put this one up next week.

230
00:12:00,260 --> 00:12:01,860
You're pretty resourceful.

231
00:12:02,090 --> 00:12:02,940
Of course.

232
00:12:08,240 --> 00:12:09,390
You still kept the tickets.

233
00:12:09,390 --> 00:12:10,440
What are these? The tickets to Beijing.

234
00:12:10,440 --> 00:12:12,440
Our tickets when we went to Beijing.

235
00:12:18,470 --> 00:12:19,670
The pilot recruitment poster.

236
00:12:19,670 --> 00:12:20,930
Why are you keeping it?

237
00:12:21,440 --> 00:12:22,770
Didn't you give it to me?

238
00:12:23,670 --> 00:12:25,670
Besides, you made me this
with good intentions.

239
00:12:25,670 --> 00:12:27,480
All my dreams are on it.

240
00:12:30,720 --> 00:12:31,580
Zhang Xiaoman,

241
00:12:33,240 --> 00:12:35,080
when we were kids, we played cockfights

242
00:12:35,080 --> 00:12:36,240
in this Mahavira Hall

243
00:12:36,240 --> 00:12:37,840
and never settled the score.

244
00:12:38,510 --> 00:12:41,400
Today,
since Xiaodan and Xia Lei are both here,

245
00:12:41,870 --> 00:12:44,130
how about we bury the hatchet over a beer?

246
00:12:44,320 --> 00:12:45,510
Watch me teach him a lesson today.

247
00:12:45,510 --> 00:12:46,510
-Come on!
- If I don't put him in his place,

248
00:12:46,510 --> 00:12:47,270
he'll never stop.

249
00:12:47,270 --> 00:12:48,720
-Come on, let's do it.
-Don't go easy on him.

250
00:12:48,720 --> 00:12:49,910
Come on, what do you want?

251
00:12:49,910 --> 00:12:51,010
Xiaoman, beat him in arm wrestling!

252
00:12:51,010 --> 00:12:51,320
Go.

253
00:12:51,440 --> 00:12:52,010
Get him.

254
00:12:55,120 --> 00:12:56,070
Ready.

255
00:12:56,830 --> 00:12:57,470
Start!

256
00:12:57,870 --> 00:12:59,080
Nice, Xiaoman!

257
00:13:00,160 --> 00:13:00,830
Xiaoman!

258
00:13:02,790 --> 00:13:03,440
Go harder!

259
00:13:05,360 --> 00:13:06,720
Get down!

260
00:13:08,550 --> 00:13:09,380
This round doesn't count!

261
00:13:09,380 --> 00:13:09,960
Best two out of three.

262
00:13:09,960 --> 00:13:10,960
Always refusing to accept defeat.

263
00:13:10,960 --> 00:13:12,420
Go another round with him?

264
00:13:12,720 --> 00:13:13,850
I bet you don't dare.

265
00:13:16,510 --> 00:13:18,870
-Alright. Ready?
-One, two, three, go!

266
00:13:21,970 --> 00:13:23,570
What are you photographing?

267
00:13:23,960 --> 00:13:25,490
What are you taking pics of?

268
00:13:26,720 --> 00:13:28,450
I'm taking photos of our plant.

269
00:13:32,430 --> 00:13:33,690
When I was in Shanghai,

270
00:13:33,840 --> 00:13:36,320
my dad told me stories
about building the plant.

271
00:13:36,320 --> 00:13:40,150
He said back then,
there were people from everywhere.

272
00:13:41,110 --> 00:13:42,750
Everyone spoke their hometown dialects

273
00:13:42,750 --> 00:13:43,880
in different tones,

274
00:13:44,200 --> 00:13:46,390
yet with the same cadence.

275
00:13:47,510 --> 00:13:48,720
I found it so amazing,

276
00:13:48,720 --> 00:13:51,150
just like building that Tower of Babel

277
00:13:51,150 --> 00:13:52,610
in the Western mythology.

278
00:13:54,960 --> 00:13:56,290
Well, when we were kids,

279
00:13:56,960 --> 00:13:58,690
all we did was mess around here.

280
00:13:58,750 --> 00:14:01,810
We had no idea
how many stories were hidden inside here.

281
00:14:02,640 --> 00:14:05,790
I just want to record them all properly.

282
00:14:07,960 --> 00:14:09,290
Take him down directly!

283
00:14:09,460 --> 00:14:10,190
Go for it!

284
00:14:10,960 --> 00:14:11,480
Come on!

285
00:14:12,100 --> 00:14:13,320
Come on, say you admit defeat.

286
00:14:13,320 --> 00:14:14,070
Good job, Xiaoman!

287
00:14:14,070 --> 00:14:15,470
Do you admit your defeat?

288
00:14:17,600 --> 00:14:18,850
-Oh, no.
-You were cheating.

289
00:14:18,850 --> 00:14:19,380
Come on.

290
00:14:19,880 --> 00:14:21,880
He's getting worked up again. Gosh.

291
00:14:22,670 --> 00:14:23,390
Look at you.

292
00:14:23,390 --> 00:14:24,510
He said he wanted to bury the hatchet.

293
00:14:24,510 --> 00:14:26,300
But you insisted on competing with him.

294
00:14:26,300 --> 00:14:28,160
Baldy Song rarely gets
to hang out with us.

295
00:14:28,160 --> 00:14:29,160
We had to compete.

296
00:14:29,640 --> 00:14:31,100
If it weren't for the holiday,
we wouldn't see them.

297
00:14:31,100 --> 00:14:32,150
Just like when we were kids.

298
00:14:32,150 --> 00:14:33,320
-Yeah.
-What are you looking at?

299
00:14:33,320 --> 00:14:35,040
I remember when we were kids,

300
00:14:35,060 --> 00:14:37,300
these chimneys were smoking all the time.

301
00:14:37,300 --> 00:14:38,090
Now,

302
00:14:38,510 --> 00:14:40,670
we finally see them without smoke.

303
00:14:41,440 --> 00:14:43,170
That tower, the one on the left.

304
00:14:43,510 --> 00:14:44,320
That's...

305
00:14:45,600 --> 00:14:47,730
The branch plant, yeah,
the smelting branch plant.

306
00:14:47,730 --> 00:14:48,790
From left to right,

307
00:14:49,150 --> 00:14:51,600
two smelting, one coking.

308
00:14:52,510 --> 00:14:55,770
Then Workshop 1 and Workshop 2 are
lined up behind in order.

309
00:14:56,080 --> 00:14:57,480
You know, back in school,

310
00:14:57,720 --> 00:14:59,550
Xiaoman couldn't beat me
in reciting textbooks.

311
00:14:59,550 --> 00:15:02,510
But when it came to remembering this,
he nailed it every time.

312
00:15:02,510 --> 00:15:04,150
You know what?

313
00:15:04,670 --> 00:15:07,120
I clearly remember when each chimney

314
00:15:07,120 --> 00:15:08,120
stopped smoking.

315
00:15:08,120 --> 00:15:09,450
You even remember that?

316
00:15:10,150 --> 00:15:12,810
First, this one,
the smelting plant's chimney.

317
00:15:13,510 --> 00:15:16,110
It stopped smoking
around our sophomore year.

318
00:15:16,630 --> 00:15:19,030
Then the coking plant's chimney followed.

319
00:15:19,880 --> 00:15:22,110
Next, Workshop 1 and Workshop 2

320
00:15:22,130 --> 00:15:23,580
shut down one by one.

321
00:15:34,030 --> 00:15:34,740
Xiaoman!

322
00:15:36,300 --> 00:15:37,140
Xiaoman!

323
00:15:37,920 --> 00:15:38,950
Xiaoman, are you still there?

324
00:15:38,950 --> 00:15:39,950
I saw them!

325
00:15:40,750 --> 00:15:42,000
Xiaoman!

326
00:15:43,510 --> 00:15:44,320
Xiaoman!

327
00:16:06,960 --> 00:16:09,620
Why did you stop
setting off fireworks earlier?

328
00:16:09,960 --> 00:16:11,440
I thought you had left.

329
00:16:15,510 --> 00:16:16,840
Were you waiting for me?

330
00:16:16,880 --> 00:16:18,480
No, I wasn't waiting for you.

331
00:16:19,670 --> 00:16:21,150
Then what were you waiting for?

332
00:16:21,150 --> 00:16:22,680
Waiting for the right time.

333
00:16:23,360 --> 00:16:24,080
What time?

334
00:16:25,360 --> 00:16:27,220
Do you forget what day it is today?

335
00:16:28,960 --> 00:16:29,440
Look.

336
00:16:30,510 --> 00:16:31,550
It's Friday now,

337
00:16:31,550 --> 00:16:32,460
9:17.

338
00:16:33,040 --> 00:16:35,240
Time for me to set off fireworks for you.

339
00:16:35,840 --> 00:16:36,720
Friday!

340
00:16:39,720 --> 00:16:43,360
I thought I'd never see them again.

341
00:16:45,830 --> 00:16:47,690
Why are you making it sound so sad?

342
00:16:48,140 --> 00:16:50,570
Look, this Mahavira Hall is

343
00:16:50,960 --> 00:16:51,720
right here.

344
00:16:53,320 --> 00:16:54,080
And I am

345
00:16:54,720 --> 00:16:55,650
right here, too.

346
00:16:56,360 --> 00:17:00,420
Come back anytime if you want to see it
or see me. Everything's still here.

347
00:17:26,750 --> 00:17:27,920
Why did you bring all that stuff?

348
00:17:27,920 --> 00:17:28,920
There's no room left.

349
00:17:28,920 --> 00:17:30,160
That is corn flour.

350
00:17:30,160 --> 00:17:31,350
And these are...

351
00:17:31,350 --> 00:17:32,920
-Honey fungi.
-Heimuer fungi.

352
00:17:32,920 --> 00:17:34,110
Oh, yeah, t-those are honey fungi.

353
00:17:34,110 --> 00:17:35,510
These are heimuer fungi.

354
00:17:35,550 --> 00:17:36,510
It's hard to fit everything in.

355
00:17:36,510 --> 00:17:38,860
With your dad here,
nothing's impossible to fit in.

356
00:17:38,860 --> 00:17:39,720
How can we pack more?

357
00:17:39,720 --> 00:17:40,510
-Put it in here.
-Right.

358
00:17:40,510 --> 00:17:41,960
No, no, put the clothes...
Put the clothes here.

359
00:17:41,960 --> 00:17:43,260
We don't eat these things in the dorm.

360
00:17:43,260 --> 00:17:44,480
We can't cook there.

361
00:17:44,510 --> 00:17:45,960
They're not for you.
They're for Chief Engineer Yan.

362
00:17:45,960 --> 00:17:46,680
A taste of home.

363
00:17:46,680 --> 00:17:48,340
-You know nothing.
-Exactly.

364
00:17:48,350 --> 00:17:49,420
Why should I give them to him?

365
00:17:49,420 --> 00:17:50,480
So inconsiderate.

366
00:17:51,320 --> 00:17:53,550
You're preparing so much stuff.
It's hard to carry.

367
00:17:53,550 --> 00:17:54,400
This is so heavy.

368
00:17:54,400 --> 00:17:55,510
It's not heavy. Not at all.

369
00:17:55,510 --> 00:17:57,110
I can fit much more in for you.

370
00:17:57,200 --> 00:17:58,160
They're for you!

371
00:17:58,160 --> 00:17:59,510
And you're whining about the weight?

372
00:17:59,510 --> 00:18:01,170
What else? Should I pack more?

373
00:18:01,350 --> 00:18:02,960
Should I pack some fruit for you?

374
00:18:02,960 --> 00:18:04,350
-Take some fruit then.
-Fruit? Seriously?

375
00:18:04,350 --> 00:18:07,070
-You can eat some on your way,
-It'll all spoil during the journey.

376
00:18:07,070 --> 00:18:07,830
Coming.

377
00:18:09,110 --> 00:18:09,830
I'm back.

378
00:18:09,870 --> 00:18:10,510
Welcome back, Xiaoman.

379
00:18:10,510 --> 00:18:11,510
-How's the packing?
-Finally, you're here.

380
00:18:11,510 --> 00:18:12,510
We're almost done packing.

381
00:18:12,510 --> 00:18:13,240
Good.

382
00:18:13,260 --> 00:18:14,110
What took you so long?

383
00:18:14,110 --> 00:18:15,670
I've been waiting for you for ages.

384
00:18:15,670 --> 00:18:17,280
Are you upset?
I went to buy you some food.

385
00:18:17,280 --> 00:18:19,680
Hurry and eat this popsicle. It's melting.

386
00:18:22,350 --> 00:18:23,550
I don't want to leave.

387
00:18:24,210 --> 00:18:25,480
Let me pack your things.

388
00:18:25,480 --> 00:18:27,410
It's still early. Let's wait a bit.

389
00:18:27,510 --> 00:18:29,110
It's not like you won't come back, right?

390
00:18:29,110 --> 00:18:30,040
Xia Lei, Xia Lei.

391
00:18:30,310 --> 00:18:30,920
Xia Lei!

392
00:18:34,480 --> 00:18:37,350
Xiaodan doesn't want to leave.

393
00:18:37,350 --> 00:18:38,550
Be more considerate.

394
00:18:39,070 --> 00:18:40,330
J-Just sit here for a while.

395
00:18:40,330 --> 00:18:41,330
Your mom is right.

396
00:18:41,450 --> 00:18:42,260
Move in a bit.

397
00:18:42,280 --> 00:18:43,480
Let me sit on the sofa.

398
00:18:43,960 --> 00:18:46,060
The 8-treasure porridge
goes in the suitcase.

399
00:18:46,060 --> 00:18:48,300
Six bottles of AD calcium milk go here.

400
00:18:48,330 --> 00:18:49,700
I don't want to go.

401
00:18:51,460 --> 00:18:52,910
I don't want to leave you.

402
00:18:53,350 --> 00:18:54,860
Don't you have to go back to school?

403
00:18:54,860 --> 00:18:56,190
You don't want to leave.

404
00:18:56,230 --> 00:18:57,690
But you can't stay either.

405
00:18:58,300 --> 00:19:00,070
But school takes so long.

406
00:19:02,650 --> 00:19:05,860
Look, you go back now,
and then autumn passes.

407
00:19:05,890 --> 00:19:07,550
By the time you're in your padded jacket,

408
00:19:07,550 --> 00:19:08,760
you'll be back for the New Year.

409
00:19:08,760 --> 00:19:09,390
Right?

410
00:19:11,510 --> 00:19:13,640
That will still take a long, long time.

411
00:19:17,510 --> 00:19:18,160
Oh, right.

412
00:19:18,510 --> 00:19:20,110
Could you send
the Mahavira Hall model from my place

413
00:19:20,110 --> 00:19:21,350
to Shanghai?

414
00:19:21,350 --> 00:19:22,510
It can keep me company.

415
00:19:22,510 --> 00:19:23,910
The Mahavira Hall model?

416
00:19:24,260 --> 00:19:25,460
Okay. You go first.

417
00:19:25,490 --> 00:19:27,510
And I'll find a way to deliver it to you.

418
00:19:27,510 --> 00:19:28,750
Hurry up and finish packing.

419
00:19:28,750 --> 00:19:29,850
Then we need to catch the bus.

420
00:19:29,850 --> 00:19:30,800
Otherwise, we'll be late.

421
00:19:30,800 --> 00:19:32,730
Alright, don't cry anymore, okay?

422
00:19:33,190 --> 00:19:34,650
Hurry up and pack the food.

423
00:19:37,350 --> 00:19:38,820
I'll put the fan in your bag,

424
00:19:38,820 --> 00:19:41,350
so you can use it anytime
when you feel hot on the train.

425
00:19:41,350 --> 00:19:42,880
I'm putting it here for you.

426
00:19:45,350 --> 00:19:47,300
Let's go. We're running out of time.

427
00:19:47,300 --> 00:19:47,910
Xia Lei!

428
00:19:49,870 --> 00:19:51,260
-Come on, get up.
-Let's go.

429
00:19:51,260 --> 00:19:52,960
Let's go. Come on. Get up now.

430
00:19:53,040 --> 00:19:53,700
Let's move.

431
00:19:53,960 --> 00:19:54,680
Let's go.

432
00:19:54,900 --> 00:19:55,290
Go.

433
00:19:56,110 --> 00:19:56,720
I'll carry it.

434
00:19:56,720 --> 00:19:57,480
No, no.

435
00:19:57,500 --> 00:19:58,960
Let your dad carry it. Hurry up.

436
00:19:58,960 --> 00:19:59,490
Let's go.

437
00:20:01,350 --> 00:20:02,720
Xia Lei, help us carry these.

438
00:20:02,720 --> 00:20:03,960
If you were the one who pacified her,

439
00:20:03,960 --> 00:20:04,960
we would miss the bus.

440
00:20:04,960 --> 00:20:06,290
S-Stop, don't pinch me.

441
00:20:13,960 --> 00:20:14,750
Yan,

442
00:20:14,750 --> 00:20:17,290
this is that reaction tower, right?

443
00:20:17,800 --> 00:20:18,900
It's so exquisite.

444
00:20:18,930 --> 00:20:20,350
How is it so well-made?

445
00:20:20,350 --> 00:20:21,160
What do you think, Dad?

446
00:20:21,160 --> 00:20:22,590
It's a gift from Xiaoman.

447
00:20:23,310 --> 00:20:25,840
This is much better
than that lame little boat

448
00:20:25,880 --> 00:20:27,350
he gave you before.

449
00:20:28,670 --> 00:20:29,700
This model is

450
00:20:30,350 --> 00:20:33,110
truly amazing at this level of detail.

451
00:20:33,750 --> 00:20:36,510
Xiaoman's welding proportions are precise.

452
00:20:36,910 --> 00:20:38,110
Back in our day,

453
00:20:38,430 --> 00:20:39,960
only senior welders

454
00:20:39,990 --> 00:20:41,430
could pull this off.

455
00:20:42,960 --> 00:20:44,550
When Xiaoman graduates,

456
00:20:44,550 --> 00:20:47,160
he'll definitely become
a senior welder, too.

457
00:20:47,920 --> 00:20:49,160
Yan, look, look at this.

458
00:20:49,160 --> 00:20:50,900
You used to go up and down these stairs

459
00:20:50,900 --> 00:20:52,050
every day for work.

460
00:20:52,430 --> 00:20:53,460
Sweetie, look.

461
00:20:54,350 --> 00:20:55,440
It's so well-made.

462
00:20:55,990 --> 00:20:57,190
By the way, Dad, look.

463
00:20:57,510 --> 00:20:58,910
We can even turn the light on.

464
00:20:58,910 --> 00:20:59,350
Here.

465
00:20:59,750 --> 00:21:00,350
Look.

466
00:21:00,660 --> 00:21:01,750
It can even make smoke.

467
00:21:01,750 --> 00:21:03,550
-Great.
-It looks exactly like the real thing.

468
00:21:03,550 --> 00:21:04,280
Look at this.

469
00:21:05,750 --> 00:21:07,960
I must say, Xiaoman is incredibly skilled.

470
00:21:07,960 --> 00:21:09,560
He's such a great craftsman!

471
00:21:13,450 --> 00:21:14,050
Lei.

472
00:21:15,300 --> 00:21:15,910
Lei!

473
00:21:26,320 --> 00:21:27,720
You freaked me out!

474
00:21:27,750 --> 00:21:28,640
You scared me!

475
00:21:28,660 --> 00:21:29,140
You...

476
00:21:29,170 --> 00:21:29,960
What are you doing?

477
00:21:29,960 --> 00:21:31,590
Don't you know
you can literally scare someone to death?

478
00:21:31,590 --> 00:21:32,110
I know!

479
00:21:32,110 --> 00:21:33,590
Yet you still scared me!

480
00:21:34,730 --> 00:21:37,110
I saw you had your earphones on,
and I called you so many times.

481
00:21:37,110 --> 00:21:38,110
W-What the heck.

482
00:21:39,050 --> 00:21:40,380
I paid you the mortgage.

483
00:21:40,450 --> 00:21:41,570
Don't follow me around every day

484
00:21:41,570 --> 00:21:42,510
like a loan shark.

485
00:21:42,510 --> 00:21:43,440
What do you want?

486
00:21:44,030 --> 00:21:45,030
Did I urge you to pay back?

487
00:21:45,030 --> 00:21:46,070
Did I?

488
00:21:47,050 --> 00:21:48,350
I'm doing a customer follow-up

489
00:21:48,350 --> 00:21:50,030
to check if your computer works well.

490
00:21:50,030 --> 00:21:51,030
Does it work well?

491
00:21:53,160 --> 00:21:53,790
Yeah.

492
00:21:54,650 --> 00:21:57,410
I'm using it to watch movies
and learn English.

493
00:21:58,280 --> 00:21:59,510
In this English-speaking environment,

494
00:21:59,510 --> 00:22:01,510
my English is improving like crazy.

495
00:22:01,750 --> 00:22:02,630
Right?

496
00:22:03,350 --> 00:22:05,910
But you could just use a tape recorder
to learn English.

497
00:22:05,910 --> 00:22:08,040
Isn't using a computer a bit overkill?

498
00:22:08,110 --> 00:22:09,880
I also wrote some programs.

499
00:22:10,000 --> 00:22:12,000
Got to make full use of it, you know?

500
00:22:12,430 --> 00:22:13,840
No, no, no.

501
00:22:14,780 --> 00:22:15,350
Do you remember

502
00:22:15,350 --> 00:22:16,900
when I first took you to the computer mall

503
00:22:16,900 --> 00:22:17,920
and let you feel

504
00:22:17,920 --> 00:22:19,350
the touch of the future?

505
00:22:19,450 --> 00:22:20,510
Yes, I remember it.

506
00:22:20,700 --> 00:22:22,300
BBS has helped me a lot.

507
00:22:22,760 --> 00:22:23,880
So, have you ever considered

508
00:22:23,880 --> 00:22:25,510
creating your own BBS

509
00:22:25,630 --> 00:22:26,870
to help others?

510
00:22:31,450 --> 00:22:34,050
I actually tried writing some programs,

511
00:22:34,840 --> 00:22:36,920
planning to put them

512
00:22:37,190 --> 00:22:38,590
on our school's website,

513
00:22:39,400 --> 00:22:40,600
so our fellows

514
00:22:40,750 --> 00:22:42,750
can have a platform to communicate.

515
00:22:43,930 --> 00:22:45,530
But what I made is too simple.

516
00:22:45,800 --> 00:22:46,960
It's still far from ready.

517
00:22:46,960 --> 00:22:49,110
Not at all! I think your idea is great!

518
00:22:49,110 --> 00:22:49,900
You must keep at it.

519
00:22:49,900 --> 00:22:51,100
This is a golden idea.

520
00:22:51,450 --> 00:22:52,140
C language.

521
00:22:52,960 --> 00:22:53,750
C++.

522
00:22:54,720 --> 00:22:56,470
Network theory and technology.

523
00:22:56,470 --> 00:22:57,800
Study them thoroughly.

524
00:22:59,200 --> 00:23:00,130
What do you mean?

525
00:23:00,230 --> 00:23:02,750
You have weapons but no ammunition.
This won't do!

526
00:23:02,750 --> 00:23:03,880
You need materials.

527
00:23:04,350 --> 00:23:06,280
These are all the latest versions.

528
00:23:06,400 --> 00:23:07,110
I'm back.

529
00:23:07,350 --> 00:23:08,350
How was it?

530
00:23:08,350 --> 00:23:11,110
Was the class reunion fun?

531
00:23:11,510 --> 00:23:12,840
Not interesting at all.

532
00:23:13,680 --> 00:23:14,880
Not interesting?

533
00:23:16,110 --> 00:23:17,400
Did you drink then?

534
00:23:17,750 --> 00:23:19,480
Of course I did. How could I not?

535
00:23:19,960 --> 00:23:21,200
What did you drink?

536
00:23:21,430 --> 00:23:22,060
Baijiu.

537
00:23:23,880 --> 00:23:26,520
Don't we Shanghai people
usually drink huangjiu?

538
00:23:26,520 --> 00:23:28,010
In their eyes, I'm now just

539
00:23:28,040 --> 00:23:30,350
a guy from the East Chemical Plant
in the Northeast.

540
00:23:30,350 --> 00:23:32,950
Fine then.
We'd just follow Northeast customs

541
00:23:33,160 --> 00:23:34,090
and have Baijiu.

542
00:23:34,280 --> 00:23:35,940
So what did you all talk about?

543
00:23:36,290 --> 00:23:37,300
Don't even get me started.

544
00:23:37,300 --> 00:23:39,460
I thought that at the class reunion,

545
00:23:39,480 --> 00:23:41,350
everyone would talk about the past.

546
00:23:41,350 --> 00:23:42,000
-Yeah!
-Right?

547
00:23:42,000 --> 00:23:42,900
All those fun times

548
00:23:42,900 --> 00:23:43,830
and fun stories.

549
00:23:44,670 --> 00:23:46,670
No. Nobody mentioned any of them.

550
00:23:47,710 --> 00:23:49,840
These people were all putting on airs,

551
00:23:49,960 --> 00:23:51,160
talking about things

552
00:23:51,510 --> 00:23:54,860
like how BNP Paribas set up in Pudong.

553
00:23:55,640 --> 00:23:57,380
They were chatting away excitedly.

554
00:23:57,380 --> 00:23:58,240
I mean, first of all,

555
00:23:58,240 --> 00:23:59,880
what does that have to do
with any of them?

556
00:23:59,880 --> 00:24:01,680
We don't even use French francs.

557
00:24:01,750 --> 00:24:02,590
Ridiculous.

558
00:24:03,400 --> 00:24:04,350
Alright, calm down.

559
00:24:04,350 --> 00:24:05,350
Have some water.

560
00:24:05,350 --> 00:24:05,750
It's nothing.

561
00:24:05,750 --> 00:24:07,000
I'm not angry.

562
00:24:07,000 --> 00:24:08,200
It's really nothing.

563
00:24:09,430 --> 00:24:11,680
I'm not going to these gatherings anymore.

564
00:24:11,680 --> 00:24:12,480
How boring.

565
00:24:14,000 --> 00:24:15,110
I still miss

566
00:24:16,350 --> 00:24:18,970
those old colleagues of mine
from the East Chemical Plant.

567
00:24:18,970 --> 00:24:21,930
We had so much fun chatting together.

568
00:24:22,880 --> 00:24:23,810
These people...

569
00:24:25,350 --> 00:24:26,350
Oh, this shop restocked.

570
00:24:26,350 --> 00:24:28,350
T-They're also selling
presbyopic glasses now?

571
00:24:28,350 --> 00:24:30,110
Selling instant noodles
and presbyopic glasses together?

572
00:24:30,110 --> 00:24:31,000
Why do you care?

573
00:24:33,240 --> 00:24:34,510
How much is this meat?

574
00:24:36,300 --> 00:24:36,950
Mr. Ding!

575
00:24:37,960 --> 00:24:39,290
Give me some pork belly.

576
00:24:39,350 --> 00:24:40,550
Which piece do you want?

577
00:24:40,550 --> 00:24:41,080
This one?

578
00:24:42,290 --> 00:24:44,350
Look how good this is. It has 3 layers.

579
00:24:45,510 --> 00:24:46,270
Look how fresh it is.

580
00:24:46,270 --> 00:24:47,600
Well, I w-want this one.

581
00:24:47,750 --> 00:24:49,590
What? Just this little bit?

582
00:24:50,000 --> 00:24:50,920
Mr. Ding,

583
00:24:51,590 --> 00:24:52,640
is this enough?

584
00:24:53,110 --> 00:24:55,040
I think your standard of living has

585
00:24:55,040 --> 00:24:55,960
dropped a bit lately.

586
00:24:55,960 --> 00:24:57,350
Stop your blabbering
about my standard of living.

587
00:24:57,350 --> 00:24:59,830
When has mine ever declined?

588
00:25:00,510 --> 00:25:02,030
There's no one else
dining at my home anymore.

589
00:25:02,030 --> 00:25:02,850
If I keep eating like this,

590
00:25:02,850 --> 00:25:04,830
just listening to Xia's wife will spike
my blood pressure, sugar, and lipid.

591
00:25:04,830 --> 00:25:06,000
Can I be superior to others?

592
00:25:06,000 --> 00:25:08,290
There are still
the Plant Secretary and Director!

593
00:25:08,290 --> 00:25:08,700
That's right.

594
00:25:08,700 --> 00:25:09,550
It's for Xiaoman.

595
00:25:09,550 --> 00:25:10,910
Xiaoman is still growing.

596
00:25:10,910 --> 00:25:11,930
J-Just this little bit?

597
00:25:11,930 --> 00:25:13,130
It is a bit too little.

598
00:25:14,350 --> 00:25:15,550
Here, here. This one.

599
00:25:15,920 --> 00:25:16,960
This one's good.

600
00:25:16,960 --> 00:25:18,240
T-This one's fattier.

601
00:25:19,410 --> 00:25:20,310
It's for the kid, for growing.

602
00:25:20,310 --> 00:25:21,050
It's 7.3 yuan.

603
00:25:21,050 --> 00:25:21,850
Just give me 7.

604
00:25:21,960 --> 00:25:23,350
Just let me pay the exact cost.

605
00:25:23,350 --> 00:25:24,400
Give me 7. Just 7.

606
00:25:25,320 --> 00:25:25,780
Pay me 7.

607
00:25:25,790 --> 00:25:27,620
-Alright, then.
-Liu, I'm heading back.

608
00:25:27,620 --> 00:25:28,280
7 yuan, huh?

609
00:25:32,240 --> 00:25:33,270
What's this for?

610
00:25:33,550 --> 00:25:34,820
I'm giving you this pork skin for free.

611
00:25:34,820 --> 00:25:36,280
Go home and make some aspic

612
00:25:36,350 --> 00:25:37,200
for salad.

613
00:25:37,350 --> 00:25:39,750
Consider it an extra dish
for Xiaoman from me.

614
00:25:39,750 --> 00:25:40,400
Take it.

615
00:25:40,420 --> 00:25:41,050
Thank you.

616
00:25:41,080 --> 00:25:41,590
It's okay.

617
00:25:41,590 --> 00:25:42,400
Mr. Ding.

618
00:25:42,920 --> 00:25:44,420
Are you leaving? Take care.

619
00:25:44,420 --> 00:25:46,380
I got another piece of pork skin
from your shop.

620
00:25:46,380 --> 00:25:47,320
T-Take it easy.

621
00:25:47,480 --> 00:25:48,110
Alright.

622
00:25:49,190 --> 00:25:49,880
See you.

623
00:25:50,680 --> 00:25:51,160
Bye.

624
00:25:51,440 --> 00:25:52,440
Awesome, Xia Lei.

625
00:25:52,700 --> 00:25:54,430
You're a big shot at school now.

626
00:25:55,910 --> 00:25:57,750
This is just the preliminary version.

627
00:25:57,750 --> 00:25:59,450
It still needs some debugging.

628
00:25:59,450 --> 00:26:00,290
Why so modest?

629
00:26:00,470 --> 00:26:02,210
The school computer lab is packed now.

630
00:26:02,210 --> 00:26:04,000
Everyone's flocking into it to post.

631
00:26:04,000 --> 00:26:05,110
That's right.

632
00:26:05,450 --> 00:26:07,470
Who's got a dorm as awesome as ours now?

633
00:26:07,470 --> 00:26:08,320
Look,

634
00:26:08,400 --> 00:26:10,720
we've got a computer and internet.

635
00:26:10,790 --> 00:26:13,160
Most importantly, we've got the Great Lei.

636
00:26:13,160 --> 00:26:14,750
I want to post a friend-making message.

637
00:26:14,750 --> 00:26:16,740
The one I posted yesterday
got no response all day.

638
00:26:16,740 --> 00:26:18,170
It got buried in just one afternoon.

639
00:26:18,170 --> 00:26:19,350
Today, I changed to a new pen name.

640
00:26:19,350 --> 00:26:21,350
It's called "Memories in the Wind."

641
00:26:21,590 --> 00:26:22,960
Your name has too many memories.

642
00:26:22,960 --> 00:26:24,170
No wonder no one's responded.

643
00:26:24,170 --> 00:26:25,830
How about the name "Awesome"?

644
00:26:27,080 --> 00:26:28,270
-Senior Fan.
-Senior Fan.

645
00:26:28,270 --> 00:26:28,960
What brings you here?

646
00:26:28,960 --> 00:26:29,810
Just came to see you.

647
00:26:29,810 --> 00:26:31,170
Wait, wait. Get in line.

648
00:26:31,750 --> 00:26:33,480
I'm the second shareholder. I go first.

649
00:26:33,480 --> 00:26:34,520
Then I'm third.

650
00:26:34,960 --> 00:26:37,010
Feeling a little sense of accomplishment?

651
00:26:37,010 --> 00:26:38,680
First, help me check what's up
with this mountain bike.

652
00:26:38,680 --> 00:26:40,090
Seeing them so excited,

653
00:26:40,550 --> 00:26:42,670
I'm actually feeling a bit overconfident.

654
00:26:42,670 --> 00:26:44,400
Do you want to feel even better?

655
00:26:44,960 --> 00:26:45,890
What do you mean?

656
00:26:46,750 --> 00:26:48,950
I want to take the website beyond campus

657
00:26:49,190 --> 00:26:50,300
and into the world.

658
00:26:50,820 --> 00:26:51,750
Are you running a fever?

659
00:26:51,750 --> 00:26:52,480
Nope.

660
00:26:52,870 --> 00:26:54,110
I want to build a new website,

661
00:26:54,110 --> 00:26:55,840
fuel it with commercial value,

662
00:26:55,860 --> 00:26:56,920
and sell it to the world.

663
00:26:56,920 --> 00:26:57,640
What do you think?

664
00:26:57,640 --> 00:27:00,160
I think you're even more overconfident
than I am now.

665
00:27:00,160 --> 00:27:00,960
Not at all!

666
00:27:01,900 --> 00:27:03,060
W-Will anyone actually buy it?

667
00:27:03,060 --> 00:27:04,190
Of course they will!

668
00:27:07,420 --> 00:27:09,240
Let me guess what you're thinking.

669
00:27:09,240 --> 00:27:11,440
You want me to start a business with you.

670
00:27:11,810 --> 00:27:12,870
You guessed right.

671
00:27:13,310 --> 00:27:14,000
I believe

672
00:27:14,350 --> 00:27:17,280
the internet will change every aspect
of our future.

673
00:27:17,510 --> 00:27:20,450
We're now standing at the threshold
between the past and the future.

674
00:27:20,450 --> 00:27:22,900
Lei, whether we're stepping across it

675
00:27:23,790 --> 00:27:25,120
depends on your answer.

676
00:27:35,820 --> 00:27:36,480
Here we are.

677
00:27:37,030 --> 00:27:37,720
This place?

678
00:27:40,290 --> 00:27:42,690
It's a bit rundown,
but it looks promising.

679
00:27:42,720 --> 00:27:43,720
What do you think?

680
00:27:44,160 --> 00:27:45,560
This is where we'll work.

681
00:27:46,110 --> 00:27:47,240
The whole building?

682
00:27:47,300 --> 00:27:48,500
Just one of the rooms.

683
00:27:50,110 --> 00:27:50,910
What's wrong?

684
00:27:53,590 --> 00:27:54,990
Are you crazy?

685
00:27:55,020 --> 00:27:56,130
We'll light it up!

686
00:27:56,400 --> 00:27:57,460
Let's go upstairs.

687
00:27:57,770 --> 00:27:58,550
I'll show you

688
00:27:59,250 --> 00:28:01,380
where we'll make our dreams come true.

689
00:28:03,190 --> 00:28:04,060
Slow down.

690
00:28:05,680 --> 00:28:06,700
I'm getting excited.

691
00:28:06,700 --> 00:28:07,940
I'm way too excited.

692
00:28:08,310 --> 00:28:09,710
So? Pretty hyped, right?

693
00:28:09,960 --> 00:28:10,740
Which floor is it on?

694
00:28:10,740 --> 00:28:11,480
Seventh floor.

695
00:28:11,480 --> 00:28:12,340
Seventh floor?

696
00:28:13,590 --> 00:28:14,510
777.

697
00:28:15,420 --> 00:28:16,420
What do you think?

698
00:28:16,510 --> 00:28:18,440
I specifically chose this number.

699
00:28:22,640 --> 00:28:23,270
Please.

700
00:28:27,750 --> 00:28:28,510
How is it?

701
00:28:28,960 --> 00:28:29,820
Isn't it great?

702
00:28:30,060 --> 00:28:31,720
Don't you think it's so great?

703
00:28:31,850 --> 00:28:33,510
We're already doing pretty well.

704
00:28:33,510 --> 00:28:36,350
Many companies
first start their businesses

705
00:28:36,350 --> 00:28:37,750
in garages or basements.

706
00:28:38,180 --> 00:28:40,310
We're already up here on the 7th floor.

707
00:28:40,650 --> 00:28:41,510
Look at this slogan.

708
00:28:41,510 --> 00:28:42,460
I chose it specifically.

709
00:28:42,460 --> 00:28:45,910
"Make big plans; build strong foundations;
win the future."

710
00:28:46,310 --> 00:28:47,110
What do you think?

711
00:28:47,110 --> 00:28:47,790
Not bad.

712
00:28:48,510 --> 00:28:49,590
Small as it may be,

713
00:28:49,750 --> 00:28:51,210
it has everything we need.

714
00:28:52,590 --> 00:28:54,590
The key is that the internet is fast.

715
00:28:54,960 --> 00:28:55,640
How fast?

716
00:28:55,880 --> 00:28:56,680
One megabyte.

717
00:28:57,110 --> 00:28:58,750
1024 kilobytes.

718
00:28:59,510 --> 00:29:00,170
How's that?

719
00:29:00,420 --> 00:29:02,690
You've spent so much on r-rent

720
00:29:02,710 --> 00:29:04,570
yet still got such fast internet?

721
00:29:04,590 --> 00:29:06,100
Don't worry about the money.

722
00:29:06,100 --> 00:29:07,160
That's my concern.

723
00:29:07,190 --> 00:29:09,190
[Business License
for the corporate entity]

724
00:29:08,300 --> 00:29:10,300
Registered capital, 100,000 yuan?

725
00:29:10,550 --> 00:29:12,680
Registration doesn't need that much.

726
00:29:16,880 --> 00:29:18,010
Why are you leaving?

727
00:29:21,510 --> 00:29:22,640
So what do you think?

728
00:29:22,710 --> 00:29:25,090
I just feel like we haven't
done anything yet,

729
00:29:25,090 --> 00:29:27,220
and we already invested so much money.

730
00:29:27,280 --> 00:29:29,050
I'm feeling the pressure already.

731
00:29:29,050 --> 00:29:30,140
Pressure is good.

732
00:29:30,620 --> 00:29:32,280
Pressure begets motivation.

733
00:29:33,660 --> 00:29:35,460
How about you drop out of school?

734
00:29:35,690 --> 00:29:37,550
Focus completely on our startup.

735
00:29:37,880 --> 00:29:40,270
I heard that Microsoft's Bill Gates

736
00:29:40,400 --> 00:29:41,180
dropped out of school

737
00:29:41,180 --> 00:29:42,980
and got rich working in a garage.

738
00:29:43,230 --> 00:29:44,960
Our starting point is higher than others.

739
00:29:44,960 --> 00:29:46,960
All we need now is a college dropout.

740
00:29:48,540 --> 00:29:50,690
I have many classes at school,

741
00:29:50,720 --> 00:29:52,750
and I'm already short on time.

742
00:29:53,290 --> 00:29:55,090
Let me set up the computer first.

743
00:29:55,430 --> 00:29:56,630
I told you to drop out.

744
00:29:57,160 --> 00:29:58,760
Dear teachers and students,

745
00:29:59,110 --> 00:30:01,550
in order to inspire
our students' innovative thinking

746
00:30:01,550 --> 00:30:03,010
and practical abilities,

747
00:30:03,110 --> 00:30:05,110
the School
of Architecture and Urban Planning,

748
00:30:05,110 --> 00:30:07,510
together with the Academic Affairs Office
and Student Affairs Office,

749
00:30:07,510 --> 00:30:08,960
officially launches

750
00:30:08,960 --> 00:30:11,110
the 3rd Tongzhou Cup
Architectural Design Competition.

751
00:30:11,110 --> 00:30:12,590
The competition will be themed

752
00:30:12,590 --> 00:30:14,510
on the Harmony of Tradition and Modernity,

753
00:30:14,510 --> 00:30:16,750
exploring innovative design solutions

754
00:30:16,750 --> 00:30:18,350
with cultural heritage significance.

755
00:30:18,350 --> 00:30:21,410
All students are encouraged
to participate actively.

756
00:30:23,350 --> 00:30:25,310
Come on, students in the back, keep up!

757
00:30:25,310 --> 00:30:25,830
Okay.

758
00:30:26,750 --> 00:30:28,350
So this is that corridor?

759
00:30:28,350 --> 00:30:29,210
That corridor.

760
00:30:29,550 --> 00:30:31,510
This seems to be where the molten steel

761
00:30:31,510 --> 00:30:32,510
gets discharged.

762
00:30:32,750 --> 00:30:34,480
It flows down along this channel.

763
00:30:34,480 --> 00:30:36,140
Right, it goes down from here.

764
00:30:36,280 --> 00:30:37,540
There are photos here.

765
00:30:39,350 --> 00:30:42,510
We'll be striving hard here for life!

766
00:30:43,160 --> 00:30:45,240
This plant might not
even be able to outlast you.

767
00:30:45,240 --> 00:30:46,500
"For life"? How silly.

768
00:30:47,200 --> 00:30:48,230
Don't jinx it.

769
00:30:51,350 --> 00:30:52,070
Xiaoman.

770
00:30:52,920 --> 00:30:53,960
Starting today,

771
00:30:54,270 --> 00:30:55,800
we're officially workers.

772
00:30:56,060 --> 00:30:57,190
Do you feel excited?

773
00:30:57,750 --> 00:30:58,750
What's there to be excited about?

774
00:30:58,750 --> 00:31:00,280
Isn't this how it should be?

775
00:31:00,690 --> 00:31:01,510
Students.

776
00:31:02,750 --> 00:31:04,160
How was the tour?

777
00:31:04,160 --> 00:31:06,160
Very good.

778
00:31:06,160 --> 00:31:08,440
Then I'll share with you all

779
00:31:08,510 --> 00:31:10,510
our yesterday, today, and tomorrow.

780
00:31:10,510 --> 00:31:12,250
Yesterday, there were
technical school classes.

781
00:31:12,250 --> 00:31:14,350
Today, we're having a tour
of the plant history exhibition.

782
00:31:14,350 --> 00:31:16,750
Tomorrow, we'll be assigned to workshops.

783
00:31:18,820 --> 00:31:19,450
Guys,

784
00:31:19,640 --> 00:31:20,990
does anyone know

785
00:31:21,020 --> 00:31:23,550
why our plant is called
the Third Front Plant?

786
00:31:23,710 --> 00:31:26,110
Isn't it just because it's
a military plant far from urban areas?

787
00:31:26,110 --> 00:31:28,060
A military plant
far from cities and towns.

788
00:31:28,060 --> 00:31:29,200
That's partly right,

789
00:31:29,200 --> 00:31:30,030
but

790
00:31:30,290 --> 00:31:31,350
not entirely accurate.

791
00:31:31,350 --> 00:31:33,510
Let me show you

792
00:31:33,510 --> 00:31:35,590
around our plant's history exhibition,
okay?

793
00:31:35,590 --> 00:31:36,350
Okay.

794
00:31:36,350 --> 00:31:36,960
Let's go.

795
00:31:36,960 --> 00:31:38,160
-Let's go.
-Let's go.

796
00:31:39,880 --> 00:31:40,750
This is my grandma!

797
00:31:40,750 --> 00:31:42,110
Where is it? Where? Where is it?

798
00:31:42,110 --> 00:31:42,970
Here! This one!

799
00:31:43,250 --> 00:31:45,520
Your grandma was so beautiful.

800
00:31:45,550 --> 00:31:47,110
So beautiful. You look just like her.

801
00:31:47,110 --> 00:31:48,110
Thank you.

802
00:31:48,310 --> 00:31:49,960
We have the same photo at our house.

803
00:31:49,960 --> 00:31:51,070
You have it, too?

804
00:31:51,090 --> 00:31:51,700
Yes.

805
00:31:52,750 --> 00:31:55,110
Guess who took this photo.

806
00:31:55,350 --> 00:31:56,960
-Who took it?
-Your grandpa?

807
00:31:56,960 --> 00:31:58,760
That's right! It was my grandpa!

808
00:31:59,110 --> 00:32:00,170
Got it in one guess.

809
00:32:00,510 --> 00:32:01,350
These little braids.

810
00:32:01,350 --> 00:32:02,950
They're exactly like yours.

811
00:32:02,960 --> 00:32:03,680
Really?

812
00:32:03,700 --> 00:32:05,110
Where is your grandma then?

813
00:32:05,110 --> 00:32:07,440
My grandma didn't tell me
where she is in the photo.

814
00:32:07,440 --> 00:32:08,110
This one?

815
00:32:07,810 --> 00:32:09,940
[Cleaning cloth pads]
[Donor: Ms. He Yuexiang]

816
00:32:08,510 --> 00:32:09,790
Silly child.

817
00:32:10,160 --> 00:32:13,200
Look, given my age,

818
00:32:13,550 --> 00:32:15,410
I can't work at the plant anymore.

819
00:32:15,960 --> 00:32:18,310
The Plant Director
has been so good to our family.

820
00:32:18,310 --> 00:32:20,510
So I'm just sewing some small cloth pads

821
00:32:20,550 --> 00:32:22,510
for them to wipe their hands

822
00:32:22,510 --> 00:32:24,240
or clean the machines and such.

823
00:32:24,550 --> 00:32:27,270
Isn't this fighting alongside them, too?

824
00:32:27,550 --> 00:32:28,410
This one? This?

825
00:32:29,160 --> 00:32:30,110
That's it!

826
00:32:30,110 --> 00:32:31,110
Look at your face. Look.

827
00:32:31,110 --> 00:32:31,830
Look at this.

828
00:32:31,830 --> 00:32:33,560
It's such a big photo, isn't it?

829
00:32:34,920 --> 00:32:35,920
Isn't it this one?

830
00:32:36,310 --> 00:32:37,150
It's that one.

831
00:32:36,480 --> 00:32:40,550
[All forces supported
the Third Front Construction]

832
00:32:37,350 --> 00:32:38,750
You should ask. It must be that one.

833
00:32:38,750 --> 00:32:40,110
It definitely is.

834
00:32:40,150 --> 00:32:41,880
Did you find your grandfather?

835
00:32:42,510 --> 00:32:43,350
The persons are too small.

836
00:32:43,350 --> 00:32:44,480
Can't figure it out.

837
00:32:45,400 --> 00:32:48,060
Maybe your grandfather was the one
taking the photo.

838
00:32:48,060 --> 00:32:49,120
The photographer.

839
00:32:53,350 --> 00:32:55,290
T-This is a photo
from the Grand Military Parade!

840
00:32:55,290 --> 00:32:56,750
I once saw it in a magazine!

